reviewText: Regurgitating simple logic facts in 20 videos, with a serious lack of inspiration, creativity, and engagement – makes it a very ineffective course.   This should be a course for 7th graders.

The course itself is rather shallow with only superficial info on ERP systems. Course presentation is so slow, I had to play at almost double speed. The assignments that are part of the program are supposed to be reviewed by peer students and the review of other people's work is also part of the required activities. In my case, there were no other assignments to review and my work was never reviewed.The presenter was completely absent from the discussions, just periodically reposting the same message again and again. Very disappointing experience and a Wayne of time and money.
boring
Very basic course, only useful if you have zero knowledge/experience of  entreprise systems (ERP) and the basic functions/process of a company.

The topic is on-point based on a the course info. The reason I only gave 3 stars is because of the teaching style. I appreciate his explanation but the whiteboard marker style makes it more boring. It takes so much of the time to explain what could have been explained for just 5-7mins.

Course was very lightly attended, it took a full 3 weeks to get feedback on my submission, but that wasn't really the problem.Honestly, I feel like the presentation of the material was good, but the end of term paper was a waste of time.  It was too open ended, and peers didn't provide any feedback to get a feel for how good it was.  Rather than just write something about a made up scenario, it would have been a lot more helpful to do a "case study" type approach where the facts were given to us and we could do an analysis that could cement the learning better.
